    caption: [Carbon:phosphorus (C:P) ratios reflect the depletion of phosphorus in surface layers of temperate lakes in summer. C:P ratios in consumers, their food, and their egesta in spring and summer are compared.],
    path: "../fig/fig-2025-10-22-13-41-37.png"
  ),
  "23.17": (
    caption: [Sulfur cycles through complex chemical pathways that affect the cycling of other elements. Estimated sizes of compartments and transfers are expressed in gigatons (Gt) and Gt per year, respectively.],
    path: "../fig/fig-2025-10-22-13-42-09.png"
  ),
  "23.18": (
    caption: [Streams draining from coal mine refuse may be extremely acidic. When mine spoils are exposed to air, sulfides are oxidized to sulfate, which combines with water to produce sulfuric acid.],
    path: "../fig/fig-2025-10-22-13-42-19.png"
  ),
  "23.19": (
    caption: [Chemoautotrophic sulfur bacteria form the base of the food chain in hydrothermal vent communities. Tubeworms (Riftia pachyptila) at a Pacific hydrothermal vent rely on these bacteria to produce food.],
    path: "../fig/fig-2025-10-22-13-42-29.png"
  )
